{"questionId":"26227","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>This question compares possible designs for a new computer network between&nbsp;multiple school buildings, and whether they meet specific requirements.</strong></p>\n<p><br>A school’s administration team decides to install new fibre-optic internet cables underground.&nbsp;The school has eight buildings that need to be connected by these cables. A map of the&nbsp;school is shown below, with the internet access point of each building labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A–H</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/4d56f6cfb0f5f0d4c7035a3ef9bcdebae4800815.png\"></p>\n<p>Jonas is planning where to install the underground cables. He begins by determining the&nbsp;distances, in metres, between the underground access points in each of the buildings.</p>\n<p>He finds&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DF</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>104</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>F</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>83</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AF</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>AF</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>89</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>104</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>89</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>104</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>83</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for substitution into the cosine rule and <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for correct substitution.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AF</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>129</mn><mo> </mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>129</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26227","referenceCode":"22M.3.AHL.TZ2.2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find AF.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}